The paper deals with the problem of constructing a data structure for approximate nearest neighbor queries for curves, which involves computational geometry (cs.CG), data structures (cs.DS), and databases (cs.DB). The paper also discusses the similarity between curves using discrete Fr\'echet or dynamic time warping distance, which falls under the category of data mining (cs.DM) and machine learning (cs.SI).
